{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluators were also asked to provide a retrospective qualitative evaluation of the process, which we include in the discussion section.To measure inter-annotator agreement we calculated the Intraclass Correlation Coefficient (ICC) measure.",
    "A one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) model was fitted to the data, treating the evaluator as a random effect.",
    "From the ANOVA table, we extracted the mean squares between evaluators (MSB) and the mean squares within evaluators (MSE).",
    "The ICC was then calculated using the formula:We calculated the ICC for three metrics: accuracy, consistency, and score.",
    "As a baseline, values above 0.5 are considered to indicate moderate consistency, with 0.75 and over indicating good consistency."
  ]
}